OL,3,C'We don't want your support': Bristol
OL,4,CRovers condemns racist abuse of player
OL,6,F"Each time, the Club has sought to act
OL,7,Fin the appropriate manner. As we made
OL,8,Fclear only a few short weeks ago, we
OL,9,Fwill continue to do so."
OL,11,FDuring the Reading game, which ended
OL,12,Fin a 1-0 defeat for the Rovers, Forde
OL,13,Fwas sent off in the 55th minute for
OL,14,Fkicking the ball away following the
OL,15,Faward of a free-kick - earning him his
OL,16,Fsecond yellow card of the game.
OL,18,FBristol Rovers added that they believe
OL,19,Fthe "same old methods of 'combating'
OL,20,Fracism," the "carefully-crafted press
OL,21,Freleases" are "not working".
